
[1]obstruction

   OBSTRUC'TION, n. [L. obstructio.]

   1. The act of obstructing.

   2. Obstacle; impediment; any thing that stops or closes a way or
   channel. Bars of sand at the mouths of rivers are often obstructions to
   navigation.

   3. That which impedes progress; hinderance. disunion and party spirit
   are often obstructions to legislative measures and to public
   prosperity.

   4. A heap. [Not proper.]
